@Comment:	taking the cue from EXP , who says Chi can <read or just tell your mom the pictures> , they don't read the text. Mot fills in things that can't be discerned from pictures , like the days of the week , and she prompts Chi to tell the rest of the story. The interaction is more like an interaction with a four-year-old than with a seven-year-old. For example , Chi can't identify the strawberries. Chi speaks softly , and the sound quality is poor....
